SIMPLE: dissection
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissection
<hw>Dis*sec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dissection</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of dissecting an
animal or plant; <as>as, <ex>dissection</ex> of the human body was held
sacrilege till the time of Francis I</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: The act of separating or dividing for the
purpose of critical examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything dissected; especially, some part, or the
whole, of an animal or plant dissected so as to exhibit the structure;
an anatomical so prepared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dissection wound</b></col>, <cd>a poisoned wound incurred
during the dissection of a dead body.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissector</ent>⟦br⟧
